1. How and when to use the AutoSum command in excel?
The Autosum formula in Excel lets you calculate the total of a specific set of cells â€” usually the total of the column or the row.
Home tab > Editing group > AutoSum

2. What is the shortcut key to perform AutoSum?
The shortcut key to perform AutoSum is Alt+=.

3. How do you get rid of Formula that omits adjacent cells?
Step-1- Launch your Excel sheet and then click on File.
Step-2- Navigate to Options and then select Formulas.
Step-3- Look for Error checking rules and uncheck Formulas which omit cells in a region.
Step-4- Click OK.

4. How do you select non-adjacent cells in Excel 2016?
Just press CTRL key and select  the one cell which you want afterthat you can select the non-adjacent cells by pressing CTRL key
and also you can highlight those cells.

5. What happens if you choose a column, hold down the Alt key and press the letters
ocw in quick succession?
The column width dialogue box opens allowing you to set the exact width of the column.

6. If you right-click on a row reference number and click on Insert, where will the row
be added?
It may be:
shift cells right
shift cells down
Entire row
Entire column

